data.text:
The former president of Croatia, Stjepan Mesic, said that the European Union is the common home for the countries of the region and that NATO is the security umbrella.

Mesic, in the solemn session of the Assembly of Kosovo in honor of the 25th anniversary of the liberation from the Serbian occupying forces, said that the Kosovo Liberation Army with the help of the international community, especially NATO, prevented a mass crime in Kosovo. He also pointed out the current security challenges in the Western Balkans, especially in Kosovo and Bosnia and Herzegovina.

Mesiq emphasized that the architecture of borders in the region has ended with the declaration of Kosovo's independence.

During today's day, the Assembly of Kosovo organized a solemn session in honor of the 25th anniversary of liberation from the Serbian occupying forces, where important regional and international dignitaries and figures participated. https://kosovapress.com/osmani-ne-kuvend-kosova-meriton-anetaresimin-ne-nato
